<paragraph id="303F907EC57AFC69FF5F212A8CE0F8DF" blockId="11.[136,775,1332,1868]" pageId="11" pageNumber="577">
One colour photograph of a live specimen published by 
<bibRefCitation id="5411ED8FC57AFC69FD1E212A8C1DFAFF" author="Turak E &amp; DeVantier L" pageId="11" pageNumber="577" refId="ref11021" refString="Turak E &amp; DeVantier L (2011) Field guide to the reef-building corals of Brunei Darussalam. Fisheries Department, Ministry of Industry and Primary Resources, Government of Brunei Darussalam, 256 pp." type="book" year="2011">Turak &amp; DeVantier (2011)</bibRefCitation>
was taken in 
<collectingCountry id="4897D0EEC57AFC69FDD4214A8F10FAFF" box="[515,622,1364,1388]" name="Indonesia" pageId="11" pageNumber="577">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
; the origin of other photographs is unclear. They present this species as 
<taxonomicName id="F780EBFDC57AFC69FD26216A8DB2FA3F" baseAuthorityName="Van der Horst" baseAuthorityYear="1921" class="Anthozoa" family="Fungiidae" genus="Lithophyllon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="11" pageNumber="577" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="lobata">
<emphasis id="02F44C6CC57AFC69FD26216A8DB2FA3F" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="577">L. lobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="F780EBFDC57AFC69FE14218A8F2DFA3F" authorityName="Rehberg" authorityYear="1892" box="[451,595,1428,1452]" class="Anthozoa" family="Fungiidae" genus="Lithophyllon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="11" pageNumber="577" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="undulatum">
<emphasis id="02F44C6CC57AFC69FE14218A8F2DFA3F" box="[451,595,1428,1452]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="577">L. undulatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see Hoeksema, 1989). The 
<typeStatus id="EF3B2EDCC57AFC69FEDA21AA8C13FA5F" box="[269,365,1460,1484]" pageId="11" pageNumber="577">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="F780EBFDC57AFC69FE4E21AA8C81FA5F" baseAuthorityName="Van der Horst" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[409,511,1460,1484]" class="Anthozoa" family="Fungiidae" genus="Lithophyllon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="11" pageNumber="577" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="lobata">
<emphasis id="02F44C6CC57AFC69FE4E21AA8C81FA5F" box="[409,511,1460,1484]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="577">L. lobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are large, thin, twirled foliaceous corals with thin septa and mouths scattered over the whole upper surface, whereas specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="F780EBFDC57AFC69FD4F21EA8E79F99F" authorityName="Ditlev" authorityYear="2003" box="[664,775,1524,1548]" class="Anthozoa" family="Fungiidae" genus="Lithophyllon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="11" pageNumber="577" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="ranjithi">
<emphasis id="02F44C6CC57AFC69FD4F21EA8E79F99F" box="[664,775,1524,1548]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="577">L. ranjithi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are thick laminar corals in one plane with folded margins, thick septa, and mouths concentrated at the centre of the upper surface. 
<taxonomicName id="F780EBFDC57AFC69FEF4224A8CF0F9FF" authorityName="Ditlev" authorityYear="2003" box="[291,398,1620,1644]" class="Anthozoa" family="Fungiidae" genus="Lithophyllon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="11" pageNumber="577" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="ranjithi">
<emphasis id="02F44C6CC57AFC69FEF4224A8CF0F9FF" box="[291,398,1620,1644]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="577">L. ranjithi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from East Sabah and 
<collectingRegion id="F2445E9CC57AFC69FD0E224A8C7AF91F" country="Indonesia" name="Kalimantan Timur" pageId="11" pageNumber="577">East Kalimantan</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="5411ED8FC57AFC69FEC2226A8CDEF91F" author="Ditlev H" box="[277,416,1652,1676]" pageId="11" pageNumber="577" pagination="193 - 219" refId="ref8506" refString="Ditlev H (2003) New scleractinian corals (Cnidaria: Anthozoa) from Sabah, North Borneo. Description of one new genus and eight new species, with notes on their taxonomy and ecology. Zoologische Mededelingen Leiden, 77: 193 - 219." type="journal article" year="2003">Ditlev, 2003</bibRefCitation>
; Hoeksema et al., 2004; 
<bibRefCitation id="5411ED8FC57AFC69FD65226A8C23F93F" author="Waheed Z &amp; Hoeksema BW" pageId="11" pageNumber="577" pagination="37 - 51" refId="ref11342" refString="Waheed Z &amp; Hoeksema BW (2013) A tale of two winds: species richness patterns of reef corals around the Semporna peninsula, Malaysia. Marine Biodiversity, 43: 37 - 51." type="journal article" year="2013">Waheed &amp; Hoeksema, 2013</bibRefCitation>
), and it has also been observed in the Kudat region at north Sabah and at Layang-Layang atoll in the South 
<collectingCountry id="4897D0EEC57AFC69FECC22CA8C25F97F" box="[283,347,1748,1772]" name="China" pageId="11" pageNumber="577">China</collectingCountry>
Sea (Waheed &amp; Hoeksema, in prep.). It was not found at the reefs of Kota Kinabalu (
<bibRefCitation id="5411ED8FC57AFC69FD4322EA8C45F8BF" author="Waheed Z &amp; Hoeksema BW" pageId="11" pageNumber="577" pagination="66 - 82" refId="ref11378" refString="Waheed Z &amp; Hoeksema BW (2014) Diversity patterns of scleractinian corals at Kota Kinabalu, Malaysia, in relation to exposure and depth. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 62: 66 - 82." type="journal article" year="2014">Waheed &amp; Hoeksema, 2014</bibRefCitation>
), which are only about 
<quantity id="F7783D9BC57AFC69FDEC230A8FF2F8BF" box="[571,652,1812,1836]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="577" unit="km" value="150.0">150 km</quantity>
away from 
<collectingCountry id="4897D0EEC57AFC69FF5F232A8DAFF8DF" box="[136,209,1844,1868]" name="Brunei" pageId="11" pageNumber="577">Brunei</collectingCountry>
in a NE direction.
</paragraph>
